headline: Review & Preview: It’s Only January?
summary: The index has fallen in three-consecutive weeks for its longest weekly losing streak since December 2024, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  The Nasdaq Composite fell 0.9% on the day but rose 0.9% on the month.  President Donald Trump said today that he would nominate Kevin Warsh, a former Federal Reserve governor, to replace Jerome Powell as chair of the central bank.
